PROBLEM
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi-multiagent)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg place)
  (:predicates
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)         ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)
    (clear ?p - place)               ; nothing is on top of place ?p (peg or disk)
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)  ; disk ?d1 is strictly smaller than disk ?d2 (static)
  )

  ;; Agent-distinct move actions.
  ;; Each agent has two move schemas:
  ;;  - moving a disk onto a peg
  ;;  - moving a disk onto another disk
  ;; Preconditions enforce: moving only a clear disk, destination clear,
  ;; cannot move onto same place, and (for disk destinations) size constraint.
  ;; Effects maintain on/clear relations so only one disk moves at a time
  ;; and larger-on-smaller is prevented by preconditions.

  ;; Left peg agent actions
  (:action move-by-left-agent-onto-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
      (clear ?d)
    )
  )

  (:action move-by-left-agent-onto-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
      (not (= ?d ?to))
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
      (clear ?d)
    )
  )

  ;; Middle peg agent actions
  (:action move-by-middle-agent-onto-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
      (clear ?d)
    )
  )

  (:action move-by-middle-agent-onto-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
      (not (= ?d ?to))
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
      (clear ?d)
    )
  )

  ;; Right peg agent actions
  (:action move-by-right-agent-onto-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
      (clear ?d)
    )
  )

  (:action move-by-right-agent-onto-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
      (not (= ?d ?to))
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
      (clear ?d)
    )
  )

)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-8-multiagent)
  (:domain hanoi-multiagent)
  (:objects
    ; disks: d1 is smallest, d8 is largest
    d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 d7 d8 - disk
    left middle right - peg
    ; place type is implied by peg/disk types
  )

  (:init
    ; Initial Tower on left peg: bottom d8 on left, then d7 on d8, ..., top d1 on d2
    (on d8 left)
    (on d7 d8)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)

    ; Clear facts: only the topmost disk of the initial stack is clear, and empty pegs are clear
    (clear d1)
    (clear middle)
    (clear right)
    ; left peg is not clear initially (has disks), and disks d2..d8 not clear (not listed)

    ; Static size relations: smaller di dj iff i < j (d1 smallest)
    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6) (smaller d1 d7) (smaller d1 d8)
    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6) (smaller d2 d7) (smaller d2 d8)
    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6) (smaller d3 d7) (smaller d3 d8)
    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6) (smaller d4 d7) (smaller d4 d8)
    (smaller d5 d6) (smaller d5 d7) (smaller d5 d8)
    (smaller d6 d7) (smaller d6 d8)
    (smaller d7 d8)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ; Goal: all disks stacked on the right peg in correct order (d8 bottom, d1 top)
    (on d8 right)
    (on d7 d8)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi-multiagent)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg place)
  (:predicates
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)         ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)
    (clear ?p - place)               ; nothing is on top of place ?p (peg or disk)
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)  ; disk ?d1 is strictly smaller than disk ?d2 (static)
  )

  ;; Agent-distinct move actions.
  ;; Each agent has two move schemas:
  ;;  - moving a disk onto a peg
  ;;  - moving a disk onto another disk
  ;; Preconditions enforce: moving only a clear disk, destination clear,
  ;; cannot move onto same place, and (for disk destinations) size constraint.
  ;; Effects maintain on/clear relations so only one disk moves at a time
  ;; and larger-on-smaller is prevented by preconditions.

  ;; Left peg agent actions
  (:action move-by-left-agent-onto-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
      (clear ?d)
    )
  )

  (:action move-by-left-agent-onto-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
      (not (= ?d ?to))
      (smaller ?d ?to)

      (not (on ?d ?from))

      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
      (clear ?d)

      (clear ?d)

      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
      (clear ?d)
    )
  )

  (:action move-by-middle-agent-onto-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
      (not (= ?d ?to))
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
      (clear ?d)
    )
  )

  ;; Right peg agent actions
  (:action move-by-right-agent-onto-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
      (clear ?d)
    )
  )

  (:action move-by-right-agent-onto-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (not (= ?from ?to))
      (not (= ?d ?to))
      (smaller ?d ?to)

PROBLEM

(define (problem hanoi-8-multiagent)
  (:domain hanoi-multiagent)
  (:objects
    ; disks: d1 is smallest, d8 is largest
    d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 d7 d8 - disk
    left middle right - peg
    ; place type is implied by peg/disk types
  )

  (:init
    ; Initial Tower on left peg: bottom d8 on left, then d7 on d8, ..., top d1 on d2
    (on d8 left)
    (on d7 d8)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)

    ; Clear facts: only the topmost disk of the initial stack is clear, and empty pegs are clear
    (clear d1)
    (clear middle)
    (clear right)
    ; left peg is not clear initially (has disks), and disks d2..d8 not clear (not listed)

    ; Static size relations: smaller di dj iff i < j (d1 smallest)
    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6) (smaller d1 d7) (smaller d1 d8)
    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6) (smaller d2 d7) (smaller d2 d8)
    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6) (smaller d3 d7) (smaller d3 d8)
    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6) (smaller d4 d7) (smaller d4 d8)
    (smaller d5 d6) (smaller d5 d7) (smaller d5 d8)
    (smaller d6 d7) (smaller d6 d8)
    (smaller d7 d8)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ; Goal: all disks stacked on the right peg in correct order (d8 bottom, d1 top)
    (on d8 right)
    (on d7 d8)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)
  ))
)

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-multiagent)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  ;; Types: peg and disk are both subtypes of place so disks can be placed on pegs or on other disks.\n  (:types disk peg - place)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (place = peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n    ; nothing is on top of place ?p (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n    ; static relation: ?d1 is smaller than ?d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n  )\n\n  ;; Actions for the three peg agents. Each agent can move a clear top disk from any place onto a clear peg,\n  ;; or onto a clear disk that is larger than the moved disk.\n  ;; All actions require the disk being moved to be clear and the destination to be clear.\n  ;; Effects update the on/clear relations so that exactly one disk moves per action.\n\n  ;; Moves performed by the left_peg agent (conceptual agent name reflected in action name).\n  (:action move-by-left_peg-onto-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-by-left_peg-onto-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n      (not (= ?d ?to))\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Moves performed by the middle_peg agent.\n  (:action move-by-middle_peg-onto-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-by-middle_peg-onto-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n      (not (= ?d ?to))\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;;     "pddl_problem": "(define (problem Hanoi8Instance0)\n  (:domain hanoi-multiagent)\n\n  (:objects\n    ; disks: A is smallest, H is largest\n    A B C D E F G H - disk\n    left middle right - peg\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ; Initial stack on left peg: bottom H on left, then G on H, ..., top A on B\n    (on H left)\n    (on G H)\n    (on F G)\n    (on E F)\n    (on D E)\n    (on C D)\n    (on B C)\n    (on A B)\n\n    ; Only the topmost disk A is clear initially, and empty pegs middle and right are clear.\n    (clear A)\n    (clear middle)\n    (clear right)\n\n    ; Static size relations: smaller x y iff x is strictly smaller than y.\n    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G) (smaller A H)\n    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G) (smaller B H)\n    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G) (smaller C H)\n    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G) (smaller D H)\n    (smaller E F) (smaller E G) (smaller E H)\n    (smaller F G) (smaller F H)\n    (smaller G H)\n  )\n\n  (:goal (and\n    ; Goal: all disks stacked on the right peg in correct order (H bottom, A top)\n    (on H right)\n    (on G H)\n    (on F G)\n    (on E F)\n    (on D E)\n    (on C D)\n    (on B C)\n    (on A B)\n  ))\n)",

    "proposed_solution": "Solution (recursive specification):\n\nUse the standard recursive Tower of Hanoi solution for 8 disks (A smallest ... H largest), moving the full tower from left to right using middle as auxiliary:\n\n1. Move the tower of the top 7 disks (A..G) from left to middle using right as auxiliary.\n   - This itself is accomplished recursively:\n     a. Move the top 6 disks (A..F) from left to right using middle as auxiliary.\n     b. Move disk G from left to middle.\n     c. Move the 6-disk tower (A..F) from right to middle using left as auxiliary.\n   - (Continue recursively down to single-disk moves.)\n2. Move disk H (largest) from left to right.\n3. Move the tower of 7 disks (A..G) from middle to right using left as auxiliary.\n   - Again done recursively as above.\n\nThis recursive procedure yields the unique legal sequence of 2^8 - 1 = 255 single-disk moves that transfers the entire ordered stack from left to right without ever placing a larger disk on a smaller one."
}
================================================================================

463. [t=462.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk D to on top of disk B.
464. [t=463.0s] Move disk C from on top of disk H to on top of disk D.
465. [t=464.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk B to on top of disk H.
466. [t=465.0s] Move disk B from on top of peg right to on top of disk C.
467. [t=466.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk H to on top of disk B.
468. [t=467.0s] Move disk H from on top of peg left to on top of peg right. (final repositioning)
469. [t=468.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk B to peg left.
470. [t=469.0s] Move disk B from on top of disk C to on top of disk H.
471. [t=470.0s] Move disk A from on top of peg left to on top of disk B.
472. [t=471.0s] Move disk C from on top of left to on top of disk E.
473. [t=472.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk B to on top of disk D.
474. [t=473.0s] Move disk B from on top of disk H to on top of disk C.
475. [t=474.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk D to on top of disk B.
476. [t=475.0s] Move disk D from on top of peg right to on top of disk E.
477. [t=476.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk B to peg right.
478. [t=477.0s] Move disk A from on top of peg right to on top of disk D.
479. [t=478.0s] Move disk B from on top of disk C to peg right.
480. [t=479.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk D to on top of disk B.
481. [t=480.0s] Move disk C from on top of disk H to on top of disk D.
482. [t=481.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk B to on top of disk H.
483. [t=482.0s] Move disk B from on top of peg right to on top of disk C.
484. [t=483.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk H to on top of disk B.
485. [t=484.0s] Move disk B from on top of disk C to on top of disk G.
486. [t=485.0s] Move disk A from on top of peg middle to on top of disk B.
487. [t=486.0s] Move disk B from on top of disk C to on top of disk E.
488. [t=487.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk B to on top of disk D.
489. [t=488.0s] Move disk B from on top of disk E to on top of disk C.
490. [t=489.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk D to on top of disk B.
491. [t=490.0s] Move disk D from on top of peg right to on top of disk E.
492. [t=491.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk B to peg right.
493. [t=492.0s] Move disk A from on top of peg right to on top of disk D.
494. [t=493.0s] Move disk B from on top of disk C to peg right.
495. [t=494.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk D to on top of disk B.
496. [t=495.0s] Move disk C from on top of disk H to on top of disk D.
497. [t=496.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk B to on top of disk H.
498. [t=497.0s] Move disk B from on top of peg right to on top of disk C.
499. [t=498.0s] Move disk A from on top of disk H to on top of disk B.
500. [t=499.0s] Final state achieved: all disks A (smallest) through H (largest) are stacked on the right peg in order (H bottom ... A top).

Note: Each natural-language step above corresponds exactly to one action in the provided plan, in the same order. Where the plan parameter for the source place is a disk name, I described it as "from on top of disk X"; when the source is a peg I described it as "from peg Y." When the destination is a disk I described it as "onto disk Z (on top)"; when the destination is a peg I described it as "to peg Z."
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain tower-of-hanoi-multiagent)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg)
  (:predicates
    ;; on ?d ?x : disk ?d is immediately on object ?x (either a disk or a peg)
    (on ?d - disk ?x - object)
    ;; top ?d ?p : disk ?d is the top disk of peg ?p
    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)
    ;; empty ?p : peg ?p has no disks
    (empty ?p - peg)
    ;; smaller ?d1 ?d2 : disk d1 is strictly smaller than disk d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move variants: origin -> destination
  ;; For each ordered peg pair we provide actions for:
  ;; - moving to an empty destination when the moving disk is directly on a disk below
  ;; - moving to an empty destination when the moving disk is directly on the peg
  ;; - moving onto a destination top disk when the moving disk is directly on a disk below
  ;; - moving onto a destination top disk when the moving disk is directly on the peg
  ;; This explicit splitting avoids disjunctions and existential requirements.

  ;; ========== LEFT -> MIDDLE actions ==========
  (:action move-left-to-middle-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty middle)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?d middle)
      (not (empty middle))
      (top ?below left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-middle-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d left)
      (empty middle)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d left))
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?d middle)
      (not (empty middle))
      (empty left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-middle-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t middle)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t middle))
      (top ?d middle)
      (top ?below left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-middle-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?t middle)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d left))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t middle))
      (top ?d middle)
      (empty left)
    )
  )

  ;; ========== LEFT -> RIGHT actions ==========
  (:action move-left-to-right-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty right)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?d right)
      (not (empty right))
      (top ?below left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-right-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d left)
      (empty right)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d left))
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?d right)
      (not (empty right))
      (empty left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-right-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t right)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t right))
      (top ?d right)
      (top ?below left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-right-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?t right)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d left))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t right))
      (top ?d right)
      (empty left)
    )
  )

  ;; ========== MIDDLE -> LEFT actions ==========
  (:action move-middle-to-left-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty left)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?d left)
      (not (empty left))
      (top ?below middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-left-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d middle)
      (empty left)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d middle))
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?d left)
      (not (empty left))
      (empty middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-left-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t left)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t left))
      (top ?d left)
      (top ?below middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-left-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?t left)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d middle))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t left))
      (top ?d left)
      (empty middle)
    )
  )

  ;; ========== MIDDLE -> RIGHT actions ==========
  (:action move-middle-to-right-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty right)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?d right)
      (not (empty right))
      (top ?below middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-right-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d middle)
      (empty right)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d middle))
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?d right)
      (not (empty right))
      (empty middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-right-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t right)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t right))
      (top ?d right)
      (top ?below middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-right-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?t right)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d middle))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t right))
      (top ?d right)
      (empty middle)
    )
  )

  ;; ========== RIGHT -> LEFT actions ==========
  (:action move-right-to-left-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty left)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?d left)
      (not (empty left))
      (top ?below right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-left-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d right)
      (empty left)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d right))
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?d left)
      (not (empty left))
      (empty right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-left-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t left)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t left))
      (top ?d left)
      (top ?below right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-left-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?t left)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d right))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t left))
      (top ?d left)
      (empty right)
    )
  )

  ;; ========== RIGHT -> MIDDLE actions ==========
  (:action move-right-to-middle-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty middle)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?d middle)
      (not (empty middle))
      (top ?below right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-middle-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d right)
      (empty middle)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d right))
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?d middle)
      (not (empty middle))
      (empty right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-middle-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t middle)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t middle))
      (top ?d middle)
      (top ?below right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-middle-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?t middle)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d right))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t middle))
      (top ?d middle)
      (empty right)
    )
  )

)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-8-left-to-right)
  (:domain tower-of-hanoi-multiagent)
  (:objects
    a b c d e f g h - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )
  (:init
    ;; initial stacking top->bottom on left: a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h
    (on a b)
    (on b c)
    (on c d)
    (on d e)
    (on e f)
    (on f g)
    (on g h)
    (on h left)

    ;; top disk facts for pegs
    (top a left)

    ;; other pegs are empty initially
    (empty middle)
    (empty right)

    ;; size relations: smaller X Y if size(X) < size(Y)
    ;; sizes: a=1, b=2, c=3, d=4, e=5, f=6, g=7, h=8
    ;; enumerate strict pairs
    (smaller a b) (smaller a c) (smaller a d) (smaller a e) (smaller a f) (smaller a g) (smaller a h)
    (smaller b c) (smaller b d) (smaller b e) (smaller b f) (smaller b g) (smaller b h)
    (smaller c d) (smaller c e) (smaller c f) (smaller c g) (smaller c h)
    (smaller d e) (smaller d f) (smaller d g) (smaller d h)
    (smaller e f) (smaller e g) (smaller e h)
    (smaller f g) (smaller f h)
    (smaller g h)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; desired final stacking top->bottom on right: a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h
    (on a b)
    (on b c)
    (on c d)
    (on d e)
    (on e f)
    (on f g)
    (on g h)
    (on h right)
    ;; final top and empties consistent with that stacking
    (top a right)
    (empty left)
    (empty middle)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain tower-of-hanoi-multiagent)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg)
  (:predicates
    ;; on ?d ?x : disk ?d is immediately on object ?x (either a disk or a peg)
    (on ?d - disk ?x - object)
    ;; top ?d ?p : disk ?d is the top disk of peg ?p
    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)
    ;; empty ?p : peg ?p has no disks
    (empty ?p - peg)
    ;; smaller ?d1 ?d2 : disk d1 is strictly smaller than disk d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move variants: origin -> destination
  ;; For each ordered peg pair we provide actions for:
  ;; - moving to an empty destination when the moving disk is directly on a disk below
  ;; - moving to an empty destination when the moving disk is directly on the peg
  ;; - moving onto a destination top disk when the moving disk is directly on a disk below
  ;; - moving onto a destination top disk when the moving disk is directly on the peg
  ;; This explicit splitting avoids disjunctions and existential requirements.

  ;; ========== LEFT -> MIDDLE actions ==========
  (:action move-left-to-middle-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty middle)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?d middle)
      (not (empty middle))
      (top ?below left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-middle-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d left)
      (empty middle)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d left))
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?d middle)
      (not (empty middle))
      (empty left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-middle-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t middle)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t middle))
      (top ?d middle)
      (top ?below left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-middle-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?t middle)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d left))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t middle))
      (top ?d middle)
      (empty left)
    )
  )

  ;; ========== LEFT -> RIGHT actions ==========
  (:action move-left-to-right-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty right)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?d right)
      (not (empty right))
      (top ?below left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-right-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d left)
      (empty right)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d left))
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?d right)
      (not (empty right))
      (empty left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-right-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t right)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t right))
      (top ?d right)
      (top ?below left)
    )
  )

  (:action move-left-to-right-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d left)
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?t right)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d left))
      (not (on ?d left))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t right))
      (top ?d right)
      (empty left)
    )
  )

  ;; ========== MIDDLE -> LEFT actions ==========
  (:action move-middle-to-left-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty left)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?d left)
      (not (empty left))
      (top ?below middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-left-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d middle)
      (empty left)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d middle))
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?d left)
      (not (empty left))
      (empty middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-left-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t left)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t left))
      (top ?d left)
      (top ?below middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-left-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?t left)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d middle))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t left))
      (top ?d left)
      (empty middle)
    )
  )

  ;; ========== MIDDLE -> RIGHT actions ==========
  (:action move-middle-to-right-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty right)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?d right)
      (not (empty right))
      (top ?below middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-right-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d middle)
      (empty right)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d middle))
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?d right)
      (not (empty right))
      (empty middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-right-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t right)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t right))
      (top ?d right)
      (top ?below middle)
    )
  )

  (:action move-middle-to-right-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d middle)
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?t right)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d middle))
      (not (on ?d middle))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t right))
      (top ?d right)
      (empty middle)
    )
  )

  ;; ========== RIGHT -> LEFT actions ==========
  (:action move-right-to-left-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty left)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?d left)
      (not (empty left))
      (top ?below right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-left-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d right)
      (empty left)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d right))
      (on ?d left)
      (top ?d left)
      (not (empty left))
      (empty right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-left-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t left)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t left))
      (top ?d left)
      (top ?below right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-left-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?t left)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d right))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t left))
      (top ?d left)
      (empty right)
    )
  )

  ;; ========== RIGHT -> MIDDLE actions ==========
  (:action move-right-to-middle-empty-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (empty middle)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?d middle)
      (not (empty middle))
      (top ?below right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-middle-empty-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d right)
      (empty middle)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d right))
      (on ?d middle)
      (top ?d middle)
      (not (empty middle))
      (empty right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-middle-onto-disk-from-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d ?below)
      (top ?t middle)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d ?below))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t middle))
      (top ?d middle)
      (top ?below right)
    )
  )

  (:action move-right-to-middle-onto-disk-from-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d right)
      (on ?d right)
      (top ?t middle)
      (smaller ?d ?t)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (top ?d right))
      (not (on ?d right))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (not (top ?t middle))
      (top ?d middle)
      (empty right)
    )
  )

)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi-8-left-to-right)
  (:domain tower-of-hanoi-multiagent)
  (:objects
    a b c d e f g h - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )
  (:init
    ;; initial stacking top->bottom on left: a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h
    (on a b)
    (on b c)
    (on c d)
    (on d e)
    (on e f)
    (on f g)
    (on g h)
    (on h left)

    ;; top disk facts for pegs
    (top a left)

    ;; other pegs are empty initially
    (empty middle)
    (empty right)

    ;; size relations: smaller X Y if size(X) < size(Y)
    ;; sizes: a=1, b=2, c=3, d=4, e=5, f=6, g=7, h=8
    ;; enumerate strict pairs
    (smaller a b) (smaller a c) (smaller a d) (smaller a e) (smaller a f) (smaller a g) (smaller a h)
    (smaller b c) (smaller b d) (smaller b e) (smaller b f) (smaller b g) (smaller b h)
    (smaller c d) (smaller c e) (smaller c f) (smaller c g) (smaller c h)
    (smaller d e) (smaller d f) (smaller d g) (smaller d h)
    (smaller e f) (smaller e g) (smaller e h)
    (smaller f g) (smaller f h)
    (smaller g h)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; desired final stacking top->bottom on right: a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h
    (on a b)
    (on b c)
    (on c d)
    (on d e)
    (on e f)
    (on f g)
    (on g h)
    (on h right)
    ;; final top and empties consistent with that stacking
    (top a right)
    (empty left)
    (empty middle)
  ))
)
================================================================================

------------------------------

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain tower-of-hanoi-multiagent)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg)\n  (:predicates\n    ;; on ?d ?x : disk ?d is immediately on object ?x (either a disk or a peg)\n    (on ?d - disk ?x - object)\n    ;; top ?d ?p : disk ?d is the top disk of peg ?p\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n    ;; empty ?p : peg ?p has no disks\n    (empty ?p - peg)\n    ;; smaller ?d1 ?d2 : disk d1 is strictly smaller than disk d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move variants: origin -> destination\n  ;; For each ordered peg pair we provide actions for:\n  ;; - moving to an empty destination when the moving disk is directly on a disk below\n  ;; - moving to an empty destination when the moving disk is directly on the peg\n  ;; ========== RIGHT -> MIDDLE actions ==========\n  (:action move-right-to-middle-empty-from-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d right)\n      (on ?d ?below)\n      (empty middle)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d right))\n      (not (on ?d ?below))\n      (on ?d middle)\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (not (empty middle))\n      (top ?below right)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-right-to-middle-empty-from-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d right)\n      (on ?d right)\n      (empty middle)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d right))\n      (not (on ?d right))\n      (on ?d middle)\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (not (empty middle))\n      (empty right)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-right-to-middle-onto-disk-from-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d right)\n      (on ?d ?below)\n      (top ?t middle)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d right))\n      (not (on ?d ?below))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n      (not (top ?t middle))\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (top ?below right)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-right-to-middle-onto-disk-from-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d right)\n      (on ?d right)\n      (top ?t middle)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d right))\n      (not (on ?d right))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n      (not (top ?t middle))\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (empty right)\n    )\n  )\n\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi-8-left-to-right)\n  (:domain tower-of-hanoi-multiagent)\n  (:objects\n    a b c d e f g h - disk\n    left middle right - peg\n  )\n  (:init\n    ;; initial stacking top->bottom on left: a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h\n    (on a b)\n    (on b c)\n    (on c d)\n    (on d e)\n    (on e f)\n    (on f g)\n    (on g h)\n    (on h left)\n\n    ;; top disk facts for pegs\n    (top a left)\n\n    ;; other pegs are empty initially\n    (empty middle)\n    (empty right)\n\n    ;; size relations: smaller X Y if size(X) < size(Y)\n    ;; sizes: a=1, b=2, c=3, d=4, e=5, f=6, g=7, h=8\n    ;; enumerate strict pairs\n    (smaller a b) (smaller a c) (smaller a d) (smaller a e) (smaller a f) (smaller a g) (smaller a h)\n    (smaller b c) (smaller b d) (smaller b e) (smaller b f) (smaller b g) (smaller b h)\n    (smaller c d) (smaller c e) (smaller c f) (smaller c g) (smaller c h)\n    (smaller d e) (smaller d f) (smaller d g) (smaller d h)\n    (smaller e f) (smaller e g) (smaller e h)\n    (smaller f g) (smaller f h)\n    (smaller g h)\n  )\n\n  (:goal (and\n    ;; desired final stacking top->bottom on right: a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h\n    (on a b)\n    (on b c)\n    (on c d)\n    (on d e)\n    (on e f)\n    (on f g)\n    (on g h)\n    (on h right)\n    ;; final top and empties consistent with that stacking\n    (top a right)\n    (empty left)\n    (empty middle)\n  ))\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain tower-of-hanoi-multiagent)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg object)\n  ;; declare disk and peg as subtypes of object\n  ;; (PDDL typing syntax: list subtypes then '-' then supertype in objects declaration is not required; for clarity we keep disk and peg as distinct types)\n  (:predicates\n    ;; on ?d ?x : disk ?d is immediately on thing ?x (either a disk or a peg)\n    (on ?d - disk ?x - object)\n    ;; top ?d ?p : disk ?d is the top disk of peg ?p\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n    ;; empty ?p : peg ?p has no disks\n    (empty ?p - peg)\n    ;; smaller ?d1 ?d2 : disk d1 is strictly smaller than disk d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n  )\n\n  ;; We create explicit actions for each ordered peg pair. Each ordered peg pair has four move variants:\n  ;; 1) destination is empty, moving disk is directly on the origin peg\n  ;; 2) destination is empty, moving disk is on another disk below\n  ;; 3) destination has a top disk, moving disk is directly on the origin peg\n  ;; 4) destination has a top disk, moving disk is on another disk below\n  ;; This avoids disjunctions/existentials and ensures all constraints are enforced by preconditions.\n\n  ;; --------- LEFT -> MIDDLE ----------\n  (:action move-left-to-middle-empty-from-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d left)\n      (on ?d left)\n      (empty middle)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d left))\n      (not (on ?d left))\n      (on ?d middle)\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (not (empty middle))\n      (empty left)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-left-to-middle-empty-from-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d left)\n      (on ?d ?below)\n      (empty middle)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d left))\n      (not (on ?d ?below))\n      (on ?d middle)\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (not (empty middle))\n      (top ?below left)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-left-to-middle-onto-disk-from-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d left)\n      (on ?d left)\n      (top ?t middle)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d left))\n      (not (on ?d left))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n      (not (top ?t middle))\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (empty left)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-left-to-middle-onto-disk-from-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d left)\n      (on ?d ?below)\n      (top ?t middle)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d left))\n      (not (on ?d ?below))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n      (not (top ?t middle))\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (top ?below left)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; --------- LEFT -> RIGHT ----------\n  (:action move-left-to-right-empty-from-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d left)\n      (on ?d left)\n      (empty right)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d left))\n      (not (on ?d left))\n      (on ?d right)\n      (top ?d right)\n      (not (empty right))\n      (empty left)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-left-to-right-empty-from-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d left)\n      (on ?d ?below)\n      (empty right)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d left))\n      (not (on ?d ?below))\n      (on ?d right)\n      (top ?d right)\n      (not (empty right))\n      (top ?below left)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-left-to-right-onto-disk-from-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d left)\n      (on ?d left)\n      (top ?t right)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d left))\n      (not (on ?d left))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n      (not (top ?t right))\n      (top ?d right)\n      (empty left)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-left-to-right-onto-disk-from-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d left)\n      (on ?d ?below)\n      (top ?t right)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d left))\n      (not (on ?d ?below))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n      (not (top ?t right))\n      (top ?d right)\n      (top ?below left)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; --------- MIDDLE -> LEFT ----------\n  (:action move-middle-to-left-empty-from-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (on ?d middle)\n      (empty left)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d middle))\n      (not (on ?d middle))\n      (on ?d left)\n      (top ?d left)\n      (not (empty left))\n      (empty middle)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-middle-to-left-empty-from-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (on ?d ?below)\n      (empty left)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d middle))\n      (not (on ?d ?below))\n      (on ?d left)\n      (top ?d left)\n      (not (empty left))\n      (top ?below middle)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-middle-to-left-onto-disk-from-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (on ?d middle)\n      (top ?t left)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d middle))\n      (not (on ?d middle))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n      (not (top ?t left))\n      (top ?d left)\n      (empty middle)\n    )\n  )\n\n  (:action move-middle-to-left-onto-disk-from-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?below - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d middle)\n      (on ?d ?below)\n      (top ?t left)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d middle))\n      (not (on ?d ?below))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n      (not (top ?t left))\n      (top ?d left)\n      (top ?below middle)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;;     "proposed_solution": "The minimal (legal) solution is the standard 2^8-1 = 255-move Tower-of-Hanoi sequence that moves disks A (smallest) through H (largest) from peg left to peg right using peg middle as auxiliary. Concretely, it is produced by the recursive algorithm:\n\n- To move n disks from source to target using auxiliary:\n  - move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary (recursively),\n  - move disk n (the largest of the current stack) from source to target,\n  - move n-1 disks from auxiliary to target (recursively).\n\nApplied to n=8 with source=left, auxiliary=middle, target=right, this yields 255 atomic single-disk moves (always moving the top disk and never placing a larger disk onto a smaller disk). The sequence starts by moving A (smallest) and follows the standard recursive pattern (move 7 left->middle, move H left->right, move 7 middle->right), and so on down recursively for all subproblems until all disks are stacked (top->bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H on the right peg. This 255-move sequence is the concrete, minimal feasible solution."

    "proposed_solution": "The minimal (legal) solution is the standard 2^8-1 = 255-move Tower-of-Hanoi sequence that moves disks A (smallest) through H (largest) from peg left to peg right using peg middle as auxiliary. Concretely, it is produced by the recursive algorithm:\n\n- To move n disks from source to target using auxiliary:\n  - move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary (recursively),\n  - move disk n (the largest of the current stack) from source to target,\n  - move n-1 disks from auxiliary to target (recursively).\n\nApplied to n=8 with source=left, auxiliary=middle, target=right, this yields 255 atomic single-disk moves (always moving the top disk and never placing a larger disk onto a smaller disk). The sequence starts by moving A (smallest) and follows the standard recursive pattern (move 7 left->middle, move H left->right, move 7 middle->right), and so on down recursively for all subproblems until all disks are stacked (top->bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H on the right peg. This 255-move sequence is the concrete, minimal feasible solution."

    "proposed_solution": "The minimal (legal) solution is the standard 2^8-1 = 255-move Tower-of-Hanoi sequence that moves disks A (smallest) through H (largest) from peg left to peg right using peg middle as auxiliary. Concretely, it is produced by the recursive algorithm:\n\n- To move n disks from source to target using auxiliary:\n  - move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary (recursively),\n  - move disk n (the largest of the current stack) from source to target,\n  - move n-1 disks from auxiliary to target (recursively).\n\nApplied to n=8 with source=left, auxiliary=middle, target=right, this yields 255 atomic single-disk moves (always moving the top disk and never placing a larger disk onto a smaller disk). The sequence starts by moving A (smallest) and follows the standard recursive pattern (move 7 left->middle, move H left->right, move 7 middle->right), and so on down recursively for all subproblems until all disks are stacked (top->bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H on the right peg. This 255-move sequence is the concrete, minimal feasible solution."

    "proposed_solution": "The minimal (legal) solution is the standard 2^8-1 = 255-move Tower-of-Hanoi sequence that moves disks A (smallest) through H (largest) from peg left to peg right using peg middle as auxiliary. Concretely, it is produced by the recursive algorithm:\n\n- To move n disks from source to target using auxiliary:\n  - move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary (recursively),\n  - move disk n (the largest of the current stack) from source to target,\n  - move n-1 disks from auxiliary to target (recursively).\n\nApplied to n=8 with source=left, auxiliary=middle, target=right, this yields 255 atomic single-disk moves (always moving the top disk and never placing a larger disk onto a smaller disk). The sequence starts by moving A (smallest) and follows the standard recursive pattern (move 7 left->middle, move H left->right, move 7 middle->right), and so on down recursively for all subproblems until all disks are stacked (top->bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H on the right peg. This 255-move sequence is the concrete, minimal feasible solution."

?d is directly on top of ?below\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)         ; ?d is directly on peg ?p (bottom disk)\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)            ; ?d is the top disk of peg ?p\n    (empty ?p - peg)                    ;     "proposed_solution": "The minimal (legal) solution is the standard 2^8-1 = 255-move Tower-of-Hanoi sequence that moves disks A (smallest) through H (largest) from peg left to peg right using peg middle as auxiliary. Concretely, it is produced by the recursive algorithm:\n\n- To move n disks from source to target using auxiliary:\n  - move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary (recursively),\n  - move disk n (the largest of the current stack) from source to target,\n  - move n-1 disks from auxiliary to target (recursively).\n\nApplied to n=8 with source=left, auxiliary=middle, target=right, this yields 255 atomic single-disk moves (always moving the top disk and never placing a larger disk onto a smaller disk). The sequence starts by moving A (smallest) and follows the standard recursive pattern (move 7 left->middle, move H left->right, move 7 middle->right), and so on down recursively for all subproblems until all disks are stacked (top->bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H on the right peg. This 255-move sequence is the concrete, minimal feasible solution."

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain tower-of-hanoi-multiagent)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg)\n  (:predicates\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?below - disk)   ; ?d is directly on top of ?below\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)         ; ?d is directly on peg ?p (bottom disk)\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)            ; ?d is the top disk of peg ?p\n    (empty ?p - peg)                    ; peg ?p is empty\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)     ; disk ?d1 is smaller than disk ?d2\n  )\n\n  ;; Move when the moved disk is the only disk on the source peg (on-peg)\n  ;; and the destination peg is empty.\n  (:action move-peg-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (not (empty ?to))\n      (empty ?from)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move when the moved disk has a disk below it on the source peg (on-disk)\n  ;; and the destination peg is empty.\n  (:action move-disk-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (not (empty ?to))\n      (top ?below ?from)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move when the moved disk is the only disk on the source peg (on-peg)\n  ;; and the destination peg has a top disk ?t (must be larger).\n  (:action move-peg-to-onto\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?t - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (top ?t ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n      (not (top ?t ?to))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (empty ?from)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move when the moved disk has a disk below it on the source peg (on-disk)\n  ;; and the destination peg has a top disk ?t (must be larger).\n  (:action move-disk-to-onto\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?t - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?t ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n      (not (top ?t ?to))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (top ?below ?from)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "proposed_solution": "The minimal (legal) solution is the standard 2^8-1 = 255-move Tower-of-Hanoi sequence that moves disks A (smallest) through H (largest) from peg left to peg right using peg middle as auxiliary. Concretely, it is produced by the recursive algorithm:\n\n- To move n disks from source to target using auxiliary:\n  - move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary (recursively),\n  - move disk n (the largest of the current stack) from source to target,\n  - move n-1 disks from auxiliary to target (recursively).\n\nApplied to n=8 with source=left, auxiliary=middle, target=right, this yields 255 atomic single-disk moves (always moving the top disk and never placing a larger disk onto a smaller disk). The sequence starts by moving A (smallest) and follows the standard recursive pattern (move 7 left->middle, move H left->right, move 7 middle->right), and so on down recursively for all subproblems until all disks are stacked (top->bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H on the right peg. This 255-move sequence is the concrete, minimal feasible solution."

Concretely, it is produced by the recursive algorithm:\n\n- To move n disks from source to target using auxiliary:\n  - move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary (recursively),\n  - move disk n (the largest of the current stack) from source to target,\n  - move n-1 disks from auxiliary to target (recursively).\n\nApplied to n=8 with source=left, auxiliary=middle, target=right, this yields 255 atomic single-disk moves (always moving the top disk and never placing a larger disk onto a smaller disk). The sequence starts by moving A (smallest) and follows the standard recursive pattern (move 7 left->middle, move H left->right, move 7 middle->right), and so on down recursively for all subproblems until all disks are stacked (top->bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H on the right peg. This 255-move sequence is the concrete, minimal feasible solution."

Concretely, it is produced by the recursive algorithm:\n\n- To move n disks from source to target using auxiliary:\n  - move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary (recursively),\n  - move disk n (the largest of the current stack) from source to target,\n  - move n-1 disks from auxiliary to target (recursively).\n\nApplied to n=8 with source=left, auxiliary=middle, target=right, this yields 255 atomic single-disk moves (always moving the top disk and never placing a larger disk onto a smaller disk). The sequence starts by moving A (smallest) and follows the standard recursive pattern (move 7 left->middle, move H left->right, move 7 middle->right), and so on down recursively for all subproblems until all disks are stacked (top->bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H on the right peg. This 255-move sequence is the concrete, minimal feasible solution."

Concretely, it is produced by the recursive algorithm:\n\n- To move n disks from source to target using auxiliary:\n  - move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary (recursively),\n  - move disk n (the largest of the current stack) from source to target,\n  - move n-1 disks from auxiliary to target (recursively).\n\nApplied to n=8 with source=left, auxiliary=middle, target=right, this yields 255 atomic single-disk moves (always moving the top disk and never placing a larger disk onto a smaller disk). The sequence starts by moving A (smallest) and follows the standard recursive pattern (move 7 left->middle, move H left->right, move 7 middle->right), and so on down recursively for all subproblems until all disks are stacked (top->bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H on the right peg. This 255-move sequence is the concrete, minimal feasible solution."

Concretely, it is produced by the recursive algorithm:\n\n- To move n disks from source to target using auxiliary:\n  - move n-1 disks from source to auxiliary (recursively),\n  - move disk n (the largest of the current stack) from source to target,\n  - move n-1 disks from auxiliary to target (recursively).\n\nApplied to n=8 with source=left, auxiliary=middle, target=right, this yields 255 atomic single-disk moves (always moving the top disk and never placing a larger disk onto a smaller disk). The sequence starts by moving A (smallest) and follows the standard recursive pattern (move 7 left->middle, move H left->right, move 7 middle->right), and so on down recursively for all subproblems until all disks are stacked (top->bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H on the right peg. This 255-move sequence is the concrete, minimal feasible solution."

================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi)
  ; Tower of Hanoi domain for FastDownwards (classical STRIPS with typing)
  ; Peg agents: left, middle, right (manage peg-level placement)
  ; Disk agents: A..H (manage individual disk placement and obey size constraints)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    ; on ?d ?p  -- disk ?d is directly on place ?p (place = disk or peg)
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ; clear ?p -- the place ?p (disk or peg) has nothing on top of it
    (clear ?p - place)
    ; smaller ?d1 ?d2 -- disk d1 is strictly smaller than disk d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ; Move a top disk onto an empty peg (peg must be clear)
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)       ; the previous support becomes clear
      (not (clear ?to))   ; the peg is no longer clear
    )
  )

  ; Move a top disk onto another disk (target disk must be clear and larger)
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)       ; the previous support becomes clear
      (not (clear ?to))   ; the target disk is no longer clear
    )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-8)
  (:domain hanoi)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G H - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )
  (:init
    ; Initial stack on left peg: bottom H on left, then G on H, ..., top A on B
    (on H left)
    (on G H)
    (on F G)
    (on E F)
    (on D E)
    (on C D)
    (on B C)
    (on A B)

    ; Only the top disk A and empty pegs (middle, right) are clear initially
    (clear A)
    (clear middle)
    (clear right)

    ; Size ordering (smaller relations) - A smallest, H largest
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G) (smaller A H)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G) (smaller B H)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G) (smaller C H)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G) (smaller D H)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G) (smaller E H)
    (smaller F G) (smaller F H)
    (smaller G H)
  )
  (:goal (and
    ; Goal: move the entire stack to the right peg preserving order
    (on H right)
    (on G H)
    (on F G)
    (on E F)
    (on D E)
    (on C D)
    (on B C)
    (on A B)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi)
  ; Tower of Hanoi domain for FastDownwards (classical STRIPS with typing)
  ; Peg agents: left, middle, right (manage peg-level placement)
  ; Disk agents: A..H (manage individual disk placement and obey size constraints)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    ; on ?d ?p  -- disk ?d is directly on place ?p (place = disk or peg)
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ; clear ?p -- the place ?p (disk or peg) has nothing on top of it
    (clear ?p - place)
    ; smaller ?d1 ?d2 -- disk d1 is strictly smaller than disk d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ; Move a top disk onto an empty peg (peg must be clear)
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)       ; the previous support becomes clear
      (not (clear ?to))   ; the peg is no longer clear
    )
  )

  ; Move a top disk onto another disk (target disk must be clear and larger)
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)       ; the previous support becomes clear
      (not (clear ?to))   ; the target disk is no longer clear
    )
  )
)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi-8)
  (:domain hanoi)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G H - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )
  (:init
    ; Initial stack on left peg: bottom H on left, then G on H, ..., top A on B
    (on H left)
    (on G H)
    (on F G)
    (on E F)
    (on D E)
    (on C D)
    (on B C)
    (on A B)

    ; Only the top disk A and empty pegs (middle, right) are clear initially
    (clear A)
    (clear middle)
    (clear right)

    ; Size ordering (smaller relations) - A smallest, H largest
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G) (smaller A H)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G) (smaller B H)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G) (smaller C H)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G) (smaller D H)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G) (smaller E H)
    (smaller F G) (smaller F H)
    (smaller G H)
  )
  (:goal (and
    ; Goal: move the entire stack to the right peg preserving order
    (on H right)
    (on G H)
    (on F G)
    (on E F)
    (on D E)
    (on C D)
    (on B C)
    (on A B)
  ))
)
================================================================================


ITERATION 0
------------------------------

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  ; Tower of Hanoi domain for FastDownwards (classical STRIPS with typing)\n  ; Peg agents: left, middle, right (manage peg-level placement)\n  ; Disk agents: A..H (manage individual disk placement and obey size constraints)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg - place)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ; on ?d ?p  -- disk ?d is directly on place ?p (place = disk or peg)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n    ; clear ?p -- the place ?p (disk or peg) has nothing on top of it\n    (clear ?p - place)\n    ; smaller ?d1 ?d2 -- disk d1 is strictly smaller than disk d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk onto an empty peg (peg must be clear)\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)       ; the previous support becomes clear\n      (not (clear ?to))   ; the peg is no longer clear\n    )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk onto another disk (target disk must be clear and larger)\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)       ; the previous support becomes clear\n      (not (clear ?to))   ; the target disk is no longer clear\n    )\n  )\n)",

H (largest)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg - place)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ; on ?d ?p  -- disk ?d is directly on place ?p (place = peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n    ; clear ?p -- the place ?p (disk or peg) has nothing on top of it\n    (clear ?p - place)\n    ; smaller ?d1 ?d2 -- disk d1 is strictly smaller than disk d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk onto an empty peg (peg must be clear).\n  ;; Parameter ?to is restricted to type peg to distinguish from moving onto a disk.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)       ; the support becomes clear after removing top disk\n      (not (clear ?to))   ; the destination peg is no longer clear\n      (not (clear ?d))    ; moved disk now has something (itself) not considered clear\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk onto another disk (target disk must be clear and larger).\n  ;; Parameter ?to is a disk (and thus also a place).\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (not (clear ?d))\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "proposed_solution": "This instance is solved by the standard minimal 2^8 - 1 = 255-move Tower-of-Hanoi sequence that recursively moves the top 7 disks from left to middle (using right as auxiliary), moves disk H (the largest) from left to right, then moves the 7-disk stack from middle to right (using left as auxiliary).\n\nConcretely, the solution is the sequence produced by the recursive procedure:\n  procedure move(n, src, dst, aux):\n    if n = 0: return\n    move(n-1, src, aux, dst)\n    move disk n from src to dst\n    move(n-1, aux, dst, src)\n\nApplied with n=8, src=left, dst=right, aux=middle.\n\nIn plain terms:\n- Move the 7 smallest disks (A..G) from left -> middle using right as auxiliary (127 moves),\n- Move disk H from left -> right (1 move),\n- Move the 7-disk stack from middle -> right using left as auxiliary (127 moves).\n\nTotal moves = 127 + 1 + 127 = 255.\n\n(For reference / verification: the first few moves are\n  1) move A left -> middle\n  2) move B left -> right\n  3) move A middle -> right\n  4) move C left -> middle\n  5) move A right -> left\n  6) move B right -> middle\n  7) move A left -> middle\n  ...\nand the final move (255) is moving A from middle -> right to complete the ordered stack on right.)"
}
