NATURAL-PLAN sas_plan_1
------------------------------
Step 1 — Action (from plan): (move-to-peg a left right)
- Human-readable: Move disk A (the smallest disk, top of the left peg) from the left peg to the right peg.
- Preconditions satisfied at start: A is on left; A is the top/clear disk on the left; the right peg is clear/empty.
- Timestamp / duration: start t = 0.0, end t = 1.0 (duration = 1 time unit; action cost = 1).
- Effects (resulting state summary): 
  - Disk A is now on the right peg (A is top on right).
  - The right peg is no longer clear (it has A).
  - The left peg’s new top disk is B (the next-smallest); the left peg is no longer holding A on top.
  - Middle peg remains empty.

No other actions. Final (achieved) state after this single step: A has been moved from left to right.
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg)

  (:predicates
    ;; disk is on a place (a peg or another disk). 'object' is the universal type.
    (on ?d - disk ?p - object)
    ;; place (peg or disk) has no disk on top
    (clear ?p - object)
    ;; size ordering: smaller ?d1 ?d2 means ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a disk onto a (empty) peg
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - object ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)            ; disk ?d is sitting on ?from
      (clear ?d)               ; nothing on top of ?d (it is the top disk)
      (clear ?to)              ; destination peg top is clear
      (not (on ?d ?to))        ; forbid no-op move (from != to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)
      (not (clear ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a disk onto another disk (must be smaller than the target disk)
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - object ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)         ; size constraint: only smaller onto larger
      (not (on ?d ?to))        ; forbid no-op move
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)
      (not (clear ?to))
    )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-3)
  (:domain hanoi)
  (:objects
    p1 p2 p3 - peg
    d1 d2 d3 - disk
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial stack: all disks on peg p1 with d3 largest at bottom
    (on d3 p1)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)

    ;; clear places (top-of-stack): only the smallest disk and empty pegs
    (clear d1)
    (clear p2)
    (clear p3)

    ;; size relations: d1 < d2 < d3
    (smaller d1 d2)
    (smaller d1 d3)
    (smaller d2 d3)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; goal: same stack order but moved to peg p3
    (on d3 p3)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg)

  (:predicates
    ;; disk is on a place (a peg or another disk). 'object' is the universal type.
    (on ?d - disk ?p - object)
    ;; place (peg or disk) has no disk on top
    (clear ?p - object)
    ;; size ordering: smaller ?d1 ?d2 means ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a disk onto a (empty) peg
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - object ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)            ; disk ?d is sitting on ?from
      (clear ?d)               ; nothing on top of ?d (it is the top disk)
      (clear ?to)              ; destination peg top is clear
      (not (on ?d ?to))        ; forbid no-op move (from != to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)
      (not (clear ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a disk onto another disk (must be smaller than the target disk)
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - object ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)         ; size constraint: only smaller onto larger
      (not (on ?d ?to))        ; forbid no-op move
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)
      (not (clear ?to))
    )
  )
)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi-3)
  (:domain hanoi)
  (:objects
    p1 p2 p3 - peg
    d1 d2 d3 - disk
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial stack: all disks on peg p1 with d3 largest at bottom
    (on d3 p1)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)

    ;; clear places (top-of-stack): only the smallest disk and empty pegs
    (clear d1)
    (clear p2)
    (clear p3)

    ;; size relations: d1 < d2 < d3
    (smaller d1 d2)
    (smaller d1 d3)
    (smaller d2 d3)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; goal: same stack order but moved to peg p3
    (on d3 p3)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)
  ))
)

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk is on a place (a peg or another disk). 'object' is the universal type.\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - object)\n    ;; place (peg or disk) has no disk on top\n    (clear ?p - object)\n    ;; size ordering: smaller ?d1 ?d2 means ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk onto a (empty) peg\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - object ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)            ; disk ?d is sitting on ?from\n      (clear ?d)               ; nothing on top of ?d (it is the top disk)\n      (clear ?to)              ; destination peg top is clear\n      (not (on ?d ?to))        ; forbid no-op move (from != to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk onto another disk (must be smaller than the target disk)\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - object ?to - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)         ; size constraint: only smaller onto larger\n      (not (on ?d ?to))        ; forbid no-op move\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi-3)\n  (:domain hanoi)\n  (:objects\n    p1 p2 p3 - peg\n    d1 d2 d3 - disk\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;; initial stack: all disks on peg p1 with d3 largest at bottom\n    (on d3 p1)\n    (on d2 d3)\n    (on d1 d2)\n\n    ;; clear places (top-of-stack): only the smallest disk and empty pegs\n    (clear d1)\n    (clear p2)\n    (clear p3)\n\n    ;; size relations: d1 < d2 < d3\n    (smaller d1 d2)\n    (smaller d1 d3)\n    (smaller d2 d3)\n  )\n\n  (:goal (and\n    ;; goal: same stack order but moved to peg p3\n    (on d3 p3)\n    (on d2 d3)\n    (on d1 d2)\n  ))\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg - place\n          place)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (place = peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n    ;; nothing is on top of this place (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n    ;; size ordering: ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk onto a peg (destination is a peg)\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)        ; disk ?d sits on ?from (peg or disk)\n      (clear ?d)           ; ?d is the top disk of its stack\n      (clear ?to)          ; destination peg is clear on top\n      (not (on ?d ?to))    ; disallow no-op (already there)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)        ; the place we removed ?d from becomes clear on top\n      (not (clear ?to))    ; destination peg is no longer clear on top\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk onto another disk (destination is a disk)\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)     ; can only place smaller disk onto strictly larger disk\n      (not (on ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem Hanoi8Instance13-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi)\n  (:objects\n    left middle right - peg\n    a b c d e f g h - disk\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;; Initial stack on left peg (top -> bottom): A=a, B=b, C=c, D=d, E=e, F=f, G=g, H=h\n    ;; Represented as: top a is on left peg; b is on a; c on b; ...; h on g.\n    (on a left)\n    (on b a)\n    (on c b)\n    (on d c)\n    (on e d)\n    (on f e)\n    (on g f)\n    (on h g)\n\n    ;; Clear places: top disk a is clear, empty pegs middle and right are clear.\n    (clear a)\n    (clear middle)\n    (clear right)\n\n    ;; Size ordering: a < b < c < d < e < f < g < h\n    (smaller a b) (smaller a c) (smaller a d) (smaller a e) (smaller a f) (smaller a g) (smaller a h)\n    (smaller b c) (smaller b d) (smaller b e) (smaller b f) (smaller b g) (smaller b h)\n    (smaller c d) (smaller c e) (smaller c f) (smaller c g) (smaller c h)\n    (smaller d e) (smaller d f) (smaller d g) (smaller d h)\n    (smaller e f) (smaller e g) (smaller e h)\n    (smaller f g) (smaller f h)\n    (smaller g h)\n  )\n\n  (:goal (and\n    ;; Goal: full stack (top->bottom) a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h moved to right peg.\n    (on a right)\n    (on b a)\n    (on c b)\n    (on d c)\n    (on e d)\n    (on f e)\n    (on g f)\n    (on h g)\n  ))",
    "target_solver": "FastDownwards",
    "pddl_plan": "No plan found.",
    "syntax_errors": "terminate called after throwing an instance of 'parser::pddl::UnexpectedEOF'\n  what():  Unexpected EOF found\nAborted (core dumped)\n",
    "pddl_logs": "INFO     planner time limit: None\nINFO     planner memory limit: None\n\nINFO     Running translator.\nINFO     translator stdin: None\nINFO     translator time limit: None\nINFO     translator memory limit: None\nINFO     translator command line string: /home/emanuele/MultiAgentPlanning/.venv/bin/python3 /home/emanuele/MultiAgentPlanning/solvers/fast-downward-24.06.1/builds/release/bin/translate/translate.py results/hanoi_scaling/hanoi_8_disks/hanoi_8_disks/FastDownwards/Hanoi8Instance13/domain_1.pddl results/hanoi_scaling/hanoi_8_disks/hanoi_8_disks/FastDownwards/Hanoi8Instance13/problem_1.pddl --sas-file output.sas\nParsing...\nError: Could not parse task file: results/hanoi_scaling/hanoi_8_disks/hanoi_8_disks/FastDownwards/Hanoi8Instance13/problem_1.pddl\nReason: Missing ')'\ntranslate exit code: 31\n\nDriver aborting after translate\nINFO     Planner time: 0.09s\n",
    "history": [
        "AgentSolutionFirst"
    ],
    "proposed_solution": "Solution summary:\n- Use the standard recursive Tower of Hanoi solution (minimal-move strategy). For N = 8 disks labeled (smallest\u2192largest) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H:\n  1. Move the top 7 disks (A..G) from left to middle using right as auxiliary (recursive).\n  2. Move disk H from left to right.\n  3. Move the 7 disks (A..G) from middle to right using left as auxiliary (recursive).\n- This produces the minimal legal sequence of 2^8 - 1 = 255 single-disk moves. Each move is an ordered triple (disk, from-peg, to-peg). The classical recursive algorithm yields the explicit ordered list of 255 moves; the above description is the concrete solution strategy and yields the full move sequence when expanded recursively (move n-1, move largest, move n-1)."

Notes:
- Every line maps exactly to the corresponding plan action in the given order. Source/target labels: Left / Middle / Right refer to pegs; Disk X refers to one disk used as the support in the move.
- Timestamps assume one move per second (step k at t = k-1 s) for readability. If you prefer different durations or no timestamps, I can remove or adjust them.
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types obj)
  (:predicates
    (disk ?x - obj)           ; object is a disk
    (peg ?x - obj)            ; object is a peg
    (on ?d - obj ?x - obj)    ; disk d is directly on object x (disk or peg)
    (clear ?x - obj)          ; nothing is on top of object x
    (smaller ?d1 - obj ?d2 - obj) ; d1 is strictly smaller than d2
  )

  ;; Move a single disk onto a peg. Only the top disk of its stack may move,
  ;; and the target peg must be clear.
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d ?from ?to - obj)
    :precondition (and
      (disk ?d)
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (peg ?to)
      (clear ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
    )
  )

  ;; Move a single disk onto another disk. Target disk must be clear and larger.
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d ?from ?to - obj)
    :precondition (and
      (disk ?d)
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (disk ?to)
      (clear ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
    )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-8)
  (:domain hanoi)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G H left middle right - obj
  )
  (:init
    ;; object types
    (disk A) (disk B) (disk C) (disk D) (disk E) (disk F) (disk G) (disk H)
    (peg left) (peg middle) (peg right)

    ;; initial stack on left peg (H bottom ... A top)
    (on A B)
    (on B C)
    (on C D)
    (on D E)
    (on E F)
    (on F G)
    (on G H)
    (on H left)

    ;; clear objects: top disk A and the two empty pegs
    (clear A)
    (clear middle)
    (clear right)

    ;; size ordering: smaller X Y means X is strictly smaller than Y
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G) (smaller A H)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G) (smaller B H)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G) (smaller C H)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G) (smaller D H)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G) (smaller E H)
    (smaller F G) (smaller F H)
    (smaller G H)
  )

  ;; Goal: replicate the complete stack on the right peg (same order)
  (:goal (and
    (on A B)
    (on B C)
    (on C D)
    (on D E)
    (on E F)
    (on F G)
    (on G H)
    (on H right)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types obj)
  (:predicates
    (disk ?x - obj)           ; object is a disk
    (peg ?x - obj)            ; object is a peg
    (on ?d - obj ?x - obj)    ; disk d is directly on object x (disk or peg)
    (clear ?x - obj)          ; nothing is on top of object x
    (smaller ?d1 - obj ?d2 - obj) ; d1 is strictly smaller than d2
  )

  ;; Move a single disk onto a peg. Only the top disk of its stack may move,
  ;; and the target peg must be clear.
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d ?from ?to - obj)
    :precondition (and
      (disk ?d)
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (peg ?to)
      (clear ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
    )
  )

  ;; Move a single disk onto another disk. Target disk must be clear and larger.
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d ?from ?to - obj)
    :precondition (and
      (disk ?d)
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (disk ?to)
      (clear ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
    )
  )
)

PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi-8)
  (:domain hanoi)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G H left middle right - obj
  )
  (:init
    ;; object types
    (disk A) (disk B) (disk C) (disk D) (disk E) (disk F) (disk G) (disk H)
    (peg left) (peg middle) (peg right)

    ;; initial stack on left peg (H bottom ... A top)
    (on A B)
    (on B C)
    (on C D)
    (on D E)
    (on E F)
    (on F G)
    (on G H)
    (on H left)

    ;; clear objects: top disk A and the two empty pegs
    (clear A)
    (clear middle)
    (clear right)

    ;; size ordering: smaller X Y means X is strictly smaller than Y
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G) (smaller A H)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G) (smaller B H)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G) (smaller C H)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G) (smaller D H)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G) (smaller E H)
    (smaller F G) (smaller F H)
    (smaller G H)
  )

  ;; Goal: replicate the complete stack on the right peg (same order)
  (:goal (and
    (on A B)
    (on B C)
    (on C D)
    (on D E)
    (on E F)
    (on F G)
    (on G H)
    (on H right)
  ))
)

Move N-1 disks from Source to Aux using Target as auxiliary.\n  2. Move the largest disk (disk number N) from Source to Target.\n  3. Move N-1 disks from Aux to Target using Source as auxiliary.\n- For N = 8 (disks A smallest ... H largest), the procedure above yields the unique optimal minimal sequence of moves consisting of 2^8 - 1 = 255 single-disk moves.\n- Concretely, the top-level step is:\n  1. Move disks A..G (the 7 smallest) from left \u2192 middle (using right as auxiliary) following the recursive pattern (127 moves).\n  2. Move disk H from left \u2192 right (1 move).\n  3. Move disks A..G from middle \u2192 right (127 moves).\n- Each step is a single-disk move of the form \"move <disk> from <peg-or-disk-support> to <peg-or-disk-support>\" and always respects the rule \"never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one\".\n- Total moves: 255. ================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
Solve a Tower of Hanoi puzzle using three pegs named left, middle, and right. There are 8 disks labelled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H from smallest (A) to largest (H). Move one disk at a time and never place a larger disk on top of a smaller one. Initially, left peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H; middle peg is empty; right peg is empty. The goal configuration is: left peg is empty; middle peg is empty; right peg has (top→bottom) A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H.
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)        ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (disk or peg)
    (clear ?p - place)              ; nothing is on top of place ?p (peg or disk)
    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)   ; disk ?x is strictly smaller than disk ?y
  )

  ;; Move a top disk onto an empty peg
  (:action move-to-empty-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (clear ?to)
                    (not (= ?from ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              (clear ?from)
              (not (clear ?to))
            )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk onto another disk (must be smaller than destination)
  (:action move-onto-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (clear ?to)
                    (smaller ?d ?to)
                    (not (= ?from ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              (clear ?from)
              (not (clear ?to))
            )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-8)
  (:domain hanoi)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G H - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial stack on left (top -> bottom): A B C D E F G H
    (on A B)
    (on B C)
    (on C D)
    (on D E)
    (on E F)
    (on F G)
    (on G H)
    (on H left)

    ;; clear = nothing on top. Top disk and empty pegs are clear.
    (clear A)
    (clear middle)
    (clear right)

    ;; size ordering (A < B < C < D < E < F < G < H)
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G) (smaller A H)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G) (smaller B H)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G) (smaller C H)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G) (smaller D H)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G) (smaller E H)
    (smaller F G) (smaller F H)
    (smaller G H)
  )

  (:goal
    (and
      ;; entire stack moved to right (top -> bottom): A B C D E F G H
      (on A B)
      (on B C)
      (on C D)
      (on D E)
      (on E F)
      (on F G)
      (on G H)
      (on H right)

      ;; left and middle must be empty (no disks on them)
      (clear left)
      (clear middle)
    )
  )
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)        ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (disk or peg)
    (clear ?p - place)              ; nothing is on top of place ?p (peg or disk)
    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)   ; disk ?x is strictly smaller than disk ?y
  )

  ;; Move a top disk onto an empty peg
  (:action move-to-empty-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (clear ?to)
                    (not (= ?from ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              (clear ?from)
              (not (clear ?to))
            )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk onto another disk (must be smaller than destination)
  (:action move-onto-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (clear ?to)
                    (smaller ?d ?to)
                    (not (= ?from ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              (clear ?from)
              (not (clear ?to))
            )
  )
)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi-8)
  (:domain hanoi)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G H - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial stack on left (top -> bottom): A B C D E F G H
    (on A B)
    (on B C)
    (on C D)
    (on D E)
    (on E F)
    (on F G)
    (on G H)
    (on H left)

    ;; clear = nothing on top. Top disk and empty pegs are clear.
    (clear A)
    (clear middle)
    (clear right)

    ;; size ordering (A < B < C < D < E < F < G < H)
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G) (smaller A H)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G) (smaller B H)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G) (smaller C H)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G) (smaller D H)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G) (smaller E H)
    (smaller F G) (smaller F H)
    (smaller G H)
  )

  (:goal
    (and
      ;; entire stack moved to right (top -> bottom): A B C D E F G H
      (on A B)
      (on B C)
      (on C D)
      (on D E)
      (on E F)
      (on F G)
      (on G H)
      (on H right)

      ;; left and middle must be empty (no disks on them)
      (clear left)
      (clear middle)
    )
  )
)
